comment.shortText:
Client that interfaces with Senseye's REST API. Provides wrapper functions for
standard GET, DELETE, POST and PUT requests, as well as specific Senseye endpoints.

comment.text: Domain name or IP address of the API host. e.g. api.senseye.co[:80]
URL path prefix that'll be appended to `host`.
Authentication token or API key.

comment.shortText: Stops a running compute task.
comment.returns: A `Promise` that will produce a `ComputeTaskResponse`.

comment.text: Task ID. Can be obtained from `ComputeTaskResponse.id`.

comment.shortText:
Fetches the results of a compute task. Note this may timeout if the task
hasn't successfully completed yet. See {SenseyeApiClient.getComputeTask}.
comment.returns: A `Promise` that will produce a `ComputeResultResponse`.

comment.text: Task ID. Can be obtained from `ComputeTaskResponse.id`.

comment.shortText:
Fetches the latest status of a compute task. Use this to poll for `SUCCESS`
before calling {@link SenseyeApiClient.getComputeResult}.
comment.returns:
A `Promise` that will produce a `ComputeTaskResponse`, containing
             the task's most recent status.

comment.text: Task ID. Can be obtained from `ComputeTaskResponse.id`.

comment.shortText:
Class that models a session, facilitating the gathering and association of event
and video data generated during a participant's interaction with on-screen
stimuli, i.e. experiment or series of experiments.

comment.text:
The max number of {@link ExperimentData} that can be held
                       within any one group by the buffer. If the limit is reached,
                       a data flush will be automatically triggered ({@link Session.flushData}).

comment.shortText:
Adds experiment data into a buffer and groups them according to the specified key.
If any grouping reaches the {@link Session.bufferLimit}, a data flush will
be automatically triggered ({@link Session.flushData})).

comment.text: This should ideally be the name of the experiment the data originated from.
Data generated during an experiment.

comment.shortText: Uploads all accumulated data and flushes them from memory.
comment.returns: A `Promise` that will produce a boolean specifying whether the operaton succeeded.

`Session.id`, or `undefined` if the instance hasn't been successfully
           initialized yet ({@link Session.init}).
An array of {@link Video} tracked by the session.

comment.shortText:
Creates a session model with the specified parameters. Note this should only be
done once per instance. Ensure initialization is successful before executing
certain functions within this class, otherwise errors may be encountered.
comment.returns: A `Promise` that will produce the created session's metadata.

comment.text: Client configured to communicate with Senseye's API.

Custom username or ID of the participant. Must be unique to the

ID of a {@link Survey} to associate to the session. Will ideally be

Initializes the provided survey ({@link Survey.init}), if not done so already,
and associates it with the session.

comment.shortText: Initializes the provided video ({@link Video.init}), which associates it with the session.

comment.text: Instance of an uninitialized {@link Video}.

comment.shortText:
Starts the current session. Note a session cannot be started again once it
is started or stopped. If necessary, a new `Session` must be created.
Stops the current session and flushes all accumulated/remaining data.

comment.text:
A condition describing the session upon stopping.
                     See Constants.Condition for valid values.

exists, the previous entry values will be overwritten.

comment.shortText:
Component that initializes a session and executes a given series of experiments.
Synchronizes experiment events with video recording.

Component that uses RNCamera to record videos. Since this mainly acts as a wrapper
around RNCamera, more information regarding some of its properties may be found here:
https://react-native-camera.github.io/react-native-camera/docs/rncamera#properties.
comment.text:
Passing in a `ref` callback will provide a reference to this component with
the following functions: `startRecording()` and `stopRecording()`, which calls
`RNCamera.recordAsync(props.recordOptions)` and `RNCamera.stopRecording()`, respectively.

comment.shortText:
This experiment is used to calibrate the gaze tracking system to provide accurate
gaze information used to assess behavior in the other tasks.
Measures pupillary light reflex by manipulating the luminance of the screen
